==Probability uses==
Set limits, particularly the limit infimum and the limit supremum, are essential for probability and measure theory. Such limits are used to calculate (or prove) the probabilities and measures of other, more purposeful, sets. For the following, formula_105 is a probability space, which means formula_79 is a σ-algebra of subsets of formula_107 and formula_108 is a probability measure defined on that σ-algebra. Sets in the σ-algebra are known as events.

